Well, the movie came out and we were all proved wrong, he was incredible in it, he captured Lestat perfectly. Anne Rice even bought Newspaper space to formally and publicly apologize to him for all the things she said and commend him on what a wonderful job he did.<br>
I've seen Mos Def in a few movies now, he was in Monster's Ball and in The Italian Job as the explosives expert, bit parts but he handled them both well, I didn't know until recently he was a musician, you may end up being surprised. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub124.ezboard.com/bamicitiaverus" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.growthspurts.com/drivee/images/778221221938.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
